  "texts": [
    "Each incorrect line can only be used as a distractor once.",
    "If the corrected lines are not sufficiently similar to any of the student's incorrect lines, they will not have paired distractors.",
    "To ensure that students with limited blocks to move have an equitable learning opportunity (Fig. 2C), if the students have less than three corrected lines, CodeTailor first still matches these corrected lines with the students' incorrect lines to find potential distractors.",
    "However, if those are not available, CodeTailor converts lines with control flow keywords and the longest lines into distractor candidates.",
    "Then, CodeTailor generates the needed number of distractor blocks from these candidate lines using the LLM (Fig. 2C-P4)."
  ],
